# AI-led development workflow

AI drives implementation; humans focus on quality assurance and final decisions.

## Flow

1. **Human/AI**: Open a request as a GitHub Issue (what тАФ background, requirements, acceptance criteria)
2. **AI**: Read the issue with `gh issue view` and propose an implementation plan
3. **Human**: Review the plan and approve with `cursor:implement` on the issue
4. **AI**: Implement per the approved plan, pass tests
5. **AI**: Before opening the PR тАФ `health-checkup` (prefer fresh subagent) then `self-review` тАФ then open the PR
6. **AI**: Review the PR when it is opened (`review-pull-request`; Cursor Automation)
7. **Human**: Review behavior, Storybook, etc., and leave feedback
8. **AI**: Address review feedback when triggered (`address-pr-review`; Cursor Automation)
9. **Human**: Re-check and merge

```mermaid
flowchart TD
  A["ЁЯСдЁЯдЦ Issue (what)"] --> B["ЁЯдЦ Implementation plan"]
  B --> C["ЁЯСд cursor:implement"]
  C --> D["ЁЯдЦ implement"]
  D --> E["ЁЯдЦ health-checkup + self-review тЖТ PR"]
  E --> F["ЁЯдЦ review PR"]
  F --> G["ЁЯСд review + feedback"]
  G --> H["ЁЯдЦ address review"]
  H --> I["ЁЯСд merge"]
  I -->|periodically, after merges accumulate| J["ЁЯдЦ version-up тАФ dedicated release PR"]
  J --> A
  L["ЁЯТб continuous-improvement"] -.separate PR.-> A
  R["ЁЯФД Renovate тАФ dependency PRs (separate)"] -.-> F
```

- Do not implement before the plan is approved (`cursor:implement` on the issue).
- Do not change beyond the approved scope.
- Do not open a PR without a pre-PR `health-checkup` (prefer separate context) and `self-review`.
- Implementation steps: `implement-issue` skill. Layout: `project-structure` skill. Language: English.

## Release cycle

Periodically, after merged work accumulates, cut a release of **syakoo-lab itself**: run the
`version-up` skill as a **dedicated PR** (bump this repo's own `package.json` `version` + change
summary + release-window `health-checkup`). That PR still goes through the same pre-PR gates and
human review as feature work. Distinct from Renovate's dependency-update PRs.

## Subagents

Delegate routine work via Task. Pass only what the subagent needs.

Delegate when a step is part of this flow **and** its journey needn't be watchedтАФdelegation trims
context and, for checkup/review, keeps a **clean context**. Prefer a fresh subagent for
`health-checkup` and `self-review` before PR open. Keep `version-up` orchestration in the main agent
(it may still spawn checkup/review subagents).

| When | Subagent |
|------|----------|
| Create issue | `create-github-issue` |
| Implement | `implement-issue` |
| Before PR тАФ design health | `health-checkup` (prefer fresh subagent) |
| Before push / PR тАФ hygiene | `self-review` |
| Open PR | `create-pull-request` |
| PR opened | `review-pull-request` |
| Review feedback | `address-pr-review` |

## Automations

[cursor.com/automations](https://cursor.com/automations)

**Implement** тАФ Issue commented, `cursor:implement`, `syakoo-lab`, actor: Me. Tool: PR creation.

```text
Follow implement-issue.
```

**Review PR** тАФ Pull request opened, `syakoo/syakoo-lab`. Tool: comment only.

```text
Follow review-pull-request. Read diff, linked issue, project skills; post one review comment.
```

**Address review** тАФ Pull request commented, `cursor:address`, `syakoo/syakoo-lab`, actor: Me. Tools: comment on pull request (repo: `syakoo-lab`).

```text
Follow address-pr-review.
```

**Trigger note:** Cursor Automation fires on **general PR conversation comments** onlyтАФnot inline review comments. After leaving inline feedback, post `cursor:address` on the PR conversation to start a run. Bot comments (including the automated PR review) do not trigger automations.
